  "text": "Starting from S(123, 213, 132), here we generalize the pattern 213 considering the class S(123, 132, k(k − 1) . . . 21(k + 1)), for k ≥ 3. This class has already been described in [CITATION_1] , where the author provides the structure of its permutations. From his results, it is possible to deduce the following succession rule (similarly to Section 3, the details are omitted), encoding the construction of those permutations:",
